AGI -&nbsp;It should have helped the pilgrims to draw for Rome in the year of the Jubilee, but there is no trace of Julia. The virtual assistant was presented on 23 October during the Microsoft AI Tour, with the Ad&nbsp;Sady Nadella> and the mayor of Rome, Roberto Gualtieri, is realized in collaboration with&nbsp;Microsoft/OpenAI. >But despite the announcements of enthusiasm, the number associated with the assistant has never been spread, and at the Capitol the topic is tabù.&nbsp;
<br> Julia in intentions, was born with the aim of making tourist information more accessible, optimizing visitor flows and enhancing lesser known destinations to combat the annoying phenomenon of overturism&nbsp; in some parts of the city. Julia was presented as a system able to respond in more than 60 languages >sia in written form that spoken (so by voice, real calls or messaging channels), and that it should have been fed with data available to Roma Capitale and the major stakeholders of the city, putting it away from clickbaiting > and aggressive advertising of some search engines. All improving the overall experience of a unique tourist, cultural and commercial offer.
<br> "We are among the first in the world to make available to millions of citizens and tourists a tool with such innovative features - said the mayor Gualtieri > last October at the Eur Fountains Hall after having attended the <a href="https://www.agi.it/cronaca/news/2024-10-23/presented-julia-assistant-per-scoprire-60 "Thanks to Microsoft/OpenAI we bring artificial intelligence> to anyone who wants to experience a truly rich and personalized experience. Because Rome is turning, it is building infrastructure and upgrading its services thanks to a lot of investments that has no precedent. It is not only a museum city, but a great modern European capital and hungry for innovation.”
However, it is a pity that the traces of Julia were completely lost within four months. Only ads and promotional videos remain.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
<h2> Capital, Julia will be active in mid-March
Following the publication of this article, the City of Rome has made known through a press note that "the first release, which will be made available to users so that they can experiment and improve it through their feedback, is scheduled by the first half of March,> marking a significant milestone in the digital transformation path of the city".
Rome Capital then points out that "in these days, the final phase of automated mass testing is underway,» during which thousands of computer-generated applications simulate real usage scenarios, to ensure the reliability and efficiency of&nbsp;Julia&nbsp; in the various situations that can be presented. The official presentation of &nbsp;Julia&nbsp; will be held with an event that will explain in detail the scope of this valuable tool for promoting tourism and improving the quality of life in Rome">
&nbsp;
<h2>Lega, application for ad hoc commission on Julia and use of funds
"Despite official announcements, the contact number associated with "Julia" has never been diffused, nor is it provided with clear information on its operation, a few months from the beginning of the Jubilee 2025. This delay raises questions about the actual operation of the project and the administrative transparency." Fabrizio Santori,&nbsp;Consigliere di Roma Capitale> – Gruppo Lega Salvini Premier.
"For this reason, I asked the Commission to convene the Capitoline Tourism, Fashion and International Relations Committee to clarify the following issues:&nbsp; What is the current state of the "Julia" project and what are the timings for its actual activation? &nbsp; How many public resources have been allocated and spent to date for the development of the virtual assistant? &nbsp; From which chapter department are the funds used to finance the project? &nbsp; What are the expenditure items and how to allocate funds?<br> What are the reasons for delays in the activation of the service, which should have supported pilgrims during the Jubilee?&nbsp; The whole story seems unclear: in the face of a presentation in pump magna, the project has never been operational, and details on its economic and administrative management remain obscure. It is necessary to provide answers to citizens and ensure that public resources are used with transparency and efficiency" concludes.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
